      "amount": "3 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "soy sauce or tamari",
      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "lime juice",
      "amount": "1 tsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "crushed roasted peanuts",
      "amount": "2 tbsp",
      "notes": "for topping"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat coconut oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add onion, garlic, and ginger; sauté 3–4 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add red bell pepper and broccoli; cook 5 minutes until vegetables are tender‑crisp.",
    "Stir in red curry paste and cook 1 minute to toast the spices.",
    "Pour in coconut milk, peanut butter, and soy sauce; stir until the peanut butter fully melts and the sauce thickens.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add lime juice, taste, and adjust seasoning with extra soy sauce if needed.",
    "Serve over cooked jasmine rice (optional) and sprinkle with crushed roasted peanuts and fresh basil leaves."
  ],
